A young warrior searching for her mother,
elegantly fashioned blade in hand. Scáthach
is her twin brother, and Shannan is her cousin.
Appears in Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the
Holy War.

Prince of Isaach and descendant of the crusader
Od. Skilled wielder of the divine blade Balmung.
Appears in Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy
War.

Son of Silesse's pegasus knight Erinys. A hero
that stood up for the liberation of Munster.
Appears in Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the
Holy War.

Daughter of Quan and Ethlyn, and inheritor of
the Gáe Bolg. She was raised by her family's
enemy, Travant. Appears in Fire Emblem:
Genealogy of the Holy War.

King of Thracia, and descendant of the crusader
Dáinn. Eying the fertile land to his north, he
hatches a plan to unite the entire peninsula.
Appears in Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy
War.

A jaded dökkálfr from Dökkálfheimr, the realm
of nightmares. She delivers salacious dreams
to mortals. Though she would wish to do away
with all cloying mortal desires, she cannot.
